(1) For the purposes of type approval decisions, the manufacturer shall, upon request, provide the Ministry with a road vehicle, its system, component or separate technical unit for verification of technical requirements.

(2) Every manufacturer who is a holder of a certificate of type approval of a road vehicle or a vehicle system, vehicle component or separate technical unit of a vehicle, shall be obliged to:

- a) place on the market road vehicles or vehicle systems, vehicle components or separate technical units of a vehicle that correspond to the type for which the type approval certificate was granted;

- b) ensure production and effective control by procedures that ensure a quality management and production control system;

- c) ensure that tests of manufactured road vehicles or vehicle systems, vehicle components or separate technical units of a vehicle are carried out on test equipment designated for verifying the conformity of each manufactured road vehicle or vehicle system, vehicle component or separate technical unit of a vehicle with the issued type approval certificate;

- d) ensure that test results are recorded in test books and that test records are available for a period determined by the Ministry, but for no longer than 10 years;

- e) ensure that for each type, at least the tests required by the regulatory framework are carried out and their results analysed;

- f) ensure that after each test of samples or test parts, in which non-conformity with the issued type approval certificate is demonstrated, measures are taken to restore the conformity of the relevant production;

- g) upon the Ministry's request, provide the Ministry with a road vehicle, vehicle systems, vehicle components or separate technical units of a vehicle for verification of the continued existence of the conditions for granting the type approval certificate and enable the Ministry to verify them and provide the necessary information for this verification; after the completion of the tests, the vehicle or its part will be returned to the manufacturer, unless otherwise agreed (for example, after destructive tests);

- h) monitor the road vehicles or vehicle systems, vehicle components or separate technical units of a vehicle manufactured by them in operation and, based on analyses of failures of road vehicles or their systems, components and separate technical units, take measures to maintain their technical fitness;

- i) allow the Ministry to regularly verify the control procedures used by the manufacturer to ensure conformity;

- j) allow the Ministry to inspect production and submit test books and production records to the inspecting person and allow them to take samples for testing;

- k) ensure spare parts for at least five years after the cessation of production or import;

- l) provide anyone, upon request, with information necessary for the operation of the road vehicle and information on the technical data of the road vehicle from the time of its first entry into service.

(3) Every manufacturer who is a holder of a certificate of approval of the technical fitness of a type of road vehicle or a vehicle system, vehicle component or separate technical unit of a vehicle, shall be obliged to:

- a) place on the market road vehicles or vehicle systems, vehicle components or separate technical units of a vehicle that correspond to the type for which the type approval certificate was granted;

- b) equip the road vehicle with the vehicle identification number (VIN);

- c) ensure production and effective control by procedures that ensure a quality management and production control system;

- d) ensure that for each type, at least the tests required by the regulatory framework are carried out and their results analysed;

- e) ensure that after each test of samples or test parts, in which non-conformity with the approved type is demonstrated, measures are taken to restore the conformity of the relevant production;

- f) upon the Ministry's request, provide the Ministry with a road vehicle, vehicle systems, vehicle components or separate technical units of a vehicle for verification of the continued existence of the conditions for granting the type approval certificate and enable the Ministry to verify them and provide the necessary information for this verification;

- g) monitor the road vehicles or vehicle systems, vehicle components or separate technical units of a vehicle manufactured by them in operation and, based on analyses of failures of road vehicles or their systems, components and separate technical units, take measures to maintain their technical fitness;

- h) ensure spare parts for at least five years after the cessation of production or import;

- i) provide anyone, upon request, with information necessary for the operation of the road vehicle and information on the technical data of the road vehicle from the time of its first entry into service.

(4) The obligations of manufacturers under paragraphs 1 to 3 do not apply to manufacturers of road vehicles whose technical fitness of type has been approved pursuant to § 19, or type-approved pursuant to § 27, and manufacturers of vehicle systems, vehicle components and separate technical units of a vehicle type-approved pursuant to § 19 or § 27, with the exception of mass assembly pursuant to § 19 (2) b).

