(1) State administration and state supervision in matters concerning the conditions for the operation of vehicles on roads shall be exercised, in accordance with this Act and to the extent defined by it, and in accordance with international treaties by which the Czech Republic is bound, by the Ministry, district authorities, and the Czech Trade Inspection Authority.

(2) The Ministry shall:

- a) maintain the central register of road vehicles and the register of road vehicles of members of diplomatic missions;^4)

- b) decide on the granting, amendment, and withdrawal of technical competence for a type of road vehicle, vehicle system, vehicle component, or separate technical unit of a vehicle and road vehicle equipment;

- c) authorise a legal entity to perform activities for verifying and assessing the conformity of road vehicle properties and issuing technical protocols on such conformity;

- d) decide on the recognition of a certificate of approval of the technical competence of a type of road vehicle, vehicle system, vehicle component, or separate technical unit of a vehicle and road vehicle equipment issued by another state;

- e) decide on the granting of an exemption for the approval of the technical competence of a type of road vehicle, vehicle system, vehicle component, or separate technical unit of a vehicle and road vehicle equipment, and on the granting of an exemption for the approval of the technical competence of an individually manufactured, imported, or rebuilt road vehicle;

- f) decide on exemptions from the information document stipulated for the technical competence of a type of road vehicle in the mass production of a small series of road vehicles or individually manufactured or individually imported road vehicles;

- g) supervise the production of road vehicles, vehicle systems, vehicle components, or separate technical units of vehicles from the perspective of type technical competence approval;

- h) issue a registration certificate for a historic vehicle and issue a special registration plate for a historic vehicle;

- i) instruct manufacturers of road vehicles, vehicle systems, vehicle components, or separate technical units of vehicles on the method and deadline for rectifying deficiencies and their causes identified during production supervision from the perspective of type technical competence approval;

- j) decide on the cessation of production of road vehicles, vehicle systems, vehicle components, or separate technical units of vehicles or road vehicle equipment, or their putting into operation, if the production and operation directly endanger human life or health and road traffic safety;

- k) issue and withdraw professional certificates for inspection technicians, certificates for inspection technicians for issuing technical protocols for vehicles before their approval for operation on roads, and professional certificates for mechanics;

- l) maintain records of issued professional certificates for inspection technicians, certificates for inspection technicians for issuing technical protocols for the inspection of individual types of vehicles, interchangeable superstructures, or small series of vehicles before their approval for operation on roads, and professional certificates for mechanics;

- m) authorise technical inspection stations to perform technical inspections of individual vehicles and interchangeable superstructures before the approval of their technical competence for operation on roads;

- n) approve the technical competence of road vehicle equipment;

- o) approve the technical competence of the type of special vehicles for operation on roads;

- p) maintain a register of technical inspection stations, emission measurement stations, performed technical inspections, technical inspections of road vehicles, identification inspections of road vehicles, emission measurements, and process statistical outputs;

- r) issue and withdraw certificates of approval for measuring instruments or equipment used for performing technical inspections and emission measurements.

(3) The district authority shall:

- a) maintain the register of road vehicles;

- b) decide on the entry of a road vehicle into the vehicle register, make entries of changes to data recorded in the register;

- c) assign a registration plate to road motor vehicles and issue a registration plate;

- d) issue a registration certificate and a technical certificate for a road vehicle or a technical certificate for a road vehicle;

- e) make entries and deletions of liens on road motor vehicles in the vehicle register and the vehicle's technical certificate;

- f) decide on the decommissioning of a road vehicle;

- g) approve the technical competence of an individually manufactured or rebuilt road vehicle;

- h) approve the technical competence of an individually imported vehicle;

- i) make data entries in the technical certificate of a road vehicle;

- j) decide on the granting and withdrawal of authorisation to operate a technical inspection station;

- k) decide on the granting and withdrawal of authorisation to operate an emission measurement station;

- l) issue a certificate for the operation of a technical inspection station and an emission measurement station.

(4) The Czech Trade Inspection Authority shall inspect the quality of fuels at the manufacturer, seller, and importer in accordance with a special legal regulation^12) and monitor and supervise the quality of fuels in accordance with the implementing legal regulation issued pursuant to § 77 para. 5. The performance of analyses shall be ensured through authorised persons. The Czech Trade Inspection Authority shall be obliged to notify the Ministry of Industry and Trade monthly of the ascertained data on fuel quality for the preceding calendar month.
